# ── Build artifacts / remediation archives (Phase 22 / N2 fix) ───────────
# Tarball archives of past remediation phases should never be committed —
# they bloat the repo (119MB+ in 3 files) and create confusion with the
# live source tree. Use git history or external storage for snapshots.
*.tar.gz
*.tar.bz2
*.tgz

# ── Environment files (CRITICAL: never commit real secrets) ──────────────
# Only .env.example is tracked — it contains placeholder values for documentation.
# All other .env* files contain real secrets (DB passwords, API keys, VAPID keys,
# encryption keys) and MUST NOT be committed to version control.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
